"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The metric parameter in DBSCAN expects a callable that takes two arrays from X as input and returns a value indicating the distance between them. However, the get_point_distance function is designed to work with Point objects, not arrays. This will cause an error when DBSCAN tries to call the metric function with arrays.\",\n  \"patch\": \"24,26c24,26\\n< def get_point_distance(p1, p2):\\n<     \\\"\\\"\\\"Returns euclidean distance\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n<     return float(euclidean_distances([p1], [p2])[0, 0])\\n---\\n> def get_point_distance(p1, p2):\\n>     \\\"\\\"\\\"Returns euclidean distance\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n>     return float(euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])[0, 0])\"\n}"